        {
            "id": "intro_for_loops",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "content": "For Loops",
                    "properties": {
                        "level": 1
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "A `for` loop repeats code for each item in a sequence. It's like saying \"for each item in this list, do something.\""
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Unlike `while` loops that repeat while a condition is `True`, `for` loops repeat a specific number of times based on the items in the sequence."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "basic_for_loop",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "content": "Basic For Loop",
                    "properties": {
                        "level": 2
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "A `for` loop starts with `for`, followed by a variable name, then `in`, then a sequence, and finally a colon `:`. The code that repeats is indented."
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "The variable takes the value of each item in the sequence, one at a time, and the code inside the loop runs for each value."
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "The sequence can be a `list`, a `tuple`, a `string`, or a `range`. Lets look at a simple example with a `range`."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "for i in range(3):\n    print(f\"Number: {i}\")",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "Number: 0\nNumber: 1\nNumber: 2"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Here the variable `i` takes the value of each number in the range `0, 1, 2` one at a time, and the code inside the loop runs for each value."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "for_loop_with_range_start_stop",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "You can use `range(start, stop)` with `for` loops to control where the counting starts and stops."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "for i in range(1, 4):\n    print(f\"Number: {i}\")",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "Number: 1\nNumber: 2\nNumber: 3"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "This `for` loop starts at 1 and stops before 4, so it prints `1, 2, 3`."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "for_loop_with_range_step",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "You can also use `range(start, stop, step)` with `for` loops to control the step size."
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "**Counting by 2s**"
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "for i in range(0, 10, 2):\n    print(f\"Even number: {i}\")",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "Even number: 0\nEven number: 2\nEven number: 4\nEven number: 6\nEven number: 8"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "**Counting backwards**"
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "for i in range(5, 0, -1):\n    print(f\"Countdown: {i}\")",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "Countdown: 5\nCountdown: 4\nCountdown: 3\nCountdown: 2\nCountdown: 1"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
